 and AppKit APIs for integrating colorized symbols, as well as best practices for implementation."}],"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC21-10059-Whats-new-in-UIKit":{"role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-10059-Whats-new-in-UIKit","type":"topic","title":"What’s new in UIKit","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc21-10059-whats-new-in-uikit","abstract":[{"text":"Discover the latest updates and improvements to UIKit and learn how to build better iPadOS, iOS, and Mac Catalyst apps. We’ll take you through UI refinements, productivity updates, and API enhancements, and help you explore performance improvements and security & privacy features.","type":"text"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC21-10349-SF-Symbols-in-SwiftUI":{"role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc21-10349-sf-symbols-in-swiftui","type":"topic","kind":"article","title":"SF Symbols in SwiftUI","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Discover how you can incorporate SF Symbols into your SwiftUI app. We’ll explore basic techniques for presenting symbols, customizing their size, and showing different variants. We’ll also take you through the latest updates to symbol colorization and help you pick the right tool for your app’s needs."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-10349-SF-Symbols-in-SwiftUI"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC21-10250-Create-custom-symbols":{"role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc21-10250-create-custom-symbols","type":"topic","kind":"article","title":"Create custom symbols","abstract":[{"text":"Discover how you can create custom iconography with the latest rendering modes in SF Symbols 3. We’ll help you learn how to draw, edit, and annotate symbols, as well as explore more advanced techniques to improve the design process.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-10250-C